INSTALLING NVIM:
  $ sudo apt install neovim

  note: If it is not available on your OS, you can download from source at
          https://github.com/neovim/neovim

Setting up vim-plug:
  Go to https://github.com/junegunn/vim-plug and go to the part of
  the instructions where it explains how to install for neovim
  currently:
    $ sh -c 'curl -fLo "${XDG_DATA_HOME:-$HOME/.local/share}"/nvim/site/autoload/plug.vim --create-dirs \
      https://raw.githubusercontent.com/junegunn/vim-plug/master/plug.vim'

Setting Up your init.vim File:
  go to ./home/USERNAME/.config/ and create a new directory called nvim
    $cd ~/.config
    $ mkdir nvim

  create a file called init.vim inside the nvim directory 
  and add the contents:
    $ vi init.vim
___________________________________________
    :set number
    :set relativenumber
    :set autoindent
    :set tabstop=2
    :set softtabstop=2
    :set shiftwidth=2
    :set smarttab
    :set mouse=a

    call plug#begin()
    
    Plug 'https://github.com/vim-airline/vim-airline' " Status Bar
    Plug 'https://github.com/rafi/awesome-vim-colorschemes' " Retro 
    Plug 'https://github.com/tpope/vim-commentary'    " Commenting gcc, g
    Plug 'https://github.com/tpope/vim-surround'      " Surrpinding ysw
    Plug 'https://github.com/preservim/nerdtree'      " File viewer
    Plug 'https://github.com/tc50cal/vim-terminal'    " Terminal in nvim 
    Plug 'https://github.com/ryanoasis/vim-devicons'  " Developer Icons 
    Plug 'https://github.com/preservim/tagbar' " must run $ sudo apt instal
                                                            exuberant-ctags
    Plug 'https://github.com/neoclide/coc.nvim'       " Auto Completion 
                                                      " see bottom section
    call plug#end()     

    nnoremap <C-f> :NERDTreeFocus<CR>
    nnoremap <C-n> :NERDTree<CR>
    nnoremap <C-t> :NERDTreeToggle<CR>

    nnoremap <C-l> :TerminalSplit bash

    nmap <F8> :TagbarToggle

    :set completeopt-=preview

    :colorscheme atom

    let g:NERDTreeDirArrowExpandables="+"
    let g:NERDTreeDirArrowCollapsibles="-"

_______________________________________

  To update plugins, from inside neovim run:
    :PlugInstall

  To delete a plugin, delete from init.vim and run,
    :PlugClean


COC.NVIM: 
  To Install coc.nvim, you must have nodejs and npm installed.
  1) put the Plug command into the init.vim file and run plug install
  2) go into the file 
      $ cd ~/.config/nvim/plugged/coc.nvim
  3) run    
      $ sudo npm i -g yarn
      $ yarn install
      $ yarn build
  4) add the coc file for the language you want
      :CocInstall coc-clangd
      :CocInstall coc-python
      :CocInstall coc-snippets
     edit your snippets for each language with
      :CocCommand snippets.edit... for EACH file type
  5) set up the jedi language server by:
      $ sudo apt install python3-pip
      $ pip3 install jedi
